@baseUrl = https://localhost:7240/api
@authToken = {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### Variables
@testEmail = user@sakurahome.com
@testPassword = Test123!@#

### 1. Login to get auth token
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "{{testPassword}}"
}

### 2. Get User Activities - Page 1 (Default)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/activities
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 3. Get User Activities - Page 1 with 10 items per page
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/activities?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 4. Get User Activities - Page 2 with 20 items per page
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/activities?page=2&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 5. Get User Activities - With different page sizes
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/activities?page=1&pageSize=5
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 6. Get User Activities - Edge case: Large page size (should be capped at 100)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/activities?page=1&pageSize=500
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 7. Get User Activities - Edge case: Invalid page (should default to 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/activities?page=0&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 8. Get User Activities - Edge case: Negative values (should default to valid values)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/activities?page=-1&pageSize=-10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 9. Get User Profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 10. Get User Stats
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

